added.title: The Streak Part 1
added.description: It's Crime Season and Robin is determined to continue his streak of stopping 52 crimes every year.

added.title: I'm the Sauce
added.description: Stuck inside because of bad weather, the Titans play rainy day games after Robin convinces them that indoor activities will cheer up the clouds and make the rain stop.

added.title: Pie Bros
added.description: Beast Boy has to get a job at a pie shop to earn enough money to buy Cyborg a birthday gift, only his job interferes with being able to attend the actual party.

added.title: Hey Pizza!
added.description: Beast Boy and Cyborg try their best to slow the pizza delivery boy so they can get free pizza.

added.title: Super Robin
added.description: Robin's wish comes true and he finally gets superpowers - but at what cost?

added.title: Gorilla
added.description: Beast Boy takes over as Alpha male of the Titans when he is in Gorilla-mode and Robin has to figure out how to get back on top.

added.title: Girls' Night Out
added.description: When the guys plan a guys night out, Starfire drags Raven out on a wild adventure of their own.

added.title: You're Fired
added.description: Beast Boy gets fired from the team and the Wonder Twins take his place.

added.title: Tower Power
added.description: Cyborg plugs into the control panel of the Titans' tower and drives the others crazy.

added.title: Parasite
added.description: Starfire's new pet is a horribly dangerous parasite, but Robin is the only one who is suspicious of the beast.

added.title: Starliar
added.description: Beast Boy teaches Starfire how to lie and it backfires as her lies get more and more outrageous.

added.title: Staff Meeting
added.description: When the gang breaks Robin's beloved staff, Robin is forced to find a replacement.

added.title: Meatball Party
added.description: Raven eats a bad meatball that causes tentacles to spring from her teeth and devour the other Titans.

added.title: Grandma Voice
added.description: In order to defeat Mother Mae Eye, Cyborg starts using a grandma voice but soon that persona takes over and he begins making the other Titans dress warmly and clean their dishes.

added.title: The Rival
added.description: The Wattersons look back on Anais' first days in the Watterson house. Gumball and Darwin quickly find themselves up an opponent who is able to outsmart them at every turn.

added.title: The Lady
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin track a women emerging from their home, they discover her to be a member of a gang of wise-cracking elderly friends. However, as they get closer and closer to her life, they realize they may know her already.

added.title: The Sucker
added.description: Gumball spends the day with Bomb Kid, who has decided Gumball is the perfect target for him and his friends to play pranks on. However he soon learns that Gumball is so gullible that pranks bounce off him.

added.title: The Vegging
added.description: Gumball and Darwin want to have a lazy day on the sofa, and have come up with various tricks to stop themselves having to move. Gradually more and more people arrive, seemingly to get them to move, until finally they realize that if they have to move, they'll do it in the laziest way possible.

added.title: The One
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are joking around, but when Tobias joins in and makes fun of Gumball, he's incredibly offended. They explain to Tobias that to make those jokes he'd need to be higher on Gumball's friend list. They think that's the end of it, but Tobias is after that number one spot.

added.title: The Father
added.description: When Frankie attends a party at The Watterson's he realizes it's a holiday Granny Jojo made up to celebrate the day he left. Richard is feeling sad about the years he lost with Frankie so the kids try anything to cheer him up.

added.title: The Cringe
added.description: When the uncomfortableness between them reaches new levels, Gumball and Hot Dog Guy decide they have to confront their ongoing awkwardness by making things as awkward as possible.

added.title: The Cage
added.description: When Mr. Corneille shows up to work with a mysterious bruise, Gumball and Darwin discover that he's teacher by day and a cage fighter by night, or was until he vowed never to fight again. However, when the school is being closed for a lack of finances the boys have to try and convince him to come out retirement for one last fight.

added.title: The Faith
added.description: Everything in Elmore is suddenly just various shades of grey, and things all over town are going wrong. Gumball and Darwin follow the mayhem and learn that one person was holding the whole town together: Alan. They have to restore his faith in the world to bring color back to Elmore.

added.title: The Candidate
added.description: When their parents all go to a charity gala at the school, the kids are locked in a classroom with a VHS tape. However, when the room starts to heat up, they need a leader to get them out of the situation and have to choose between Anais, a qualified but unpopular candidate or Gumball, a charismatic candidate with absolutely no plans.

added.title: The Brain
added.description: Anais has been facepalming every time her family does something stupid, which has led to a serious medical condition. In fact, if she facepalms just one more time she could do her brain irreparable damage, so the Wattersons have to get through the week without doing anything idiotic.

added.title: The Founder
added.description: When Nicole decides to pay the cable bill in person at Chanax, she leaves specific instructions for Richard to stay in the car. However he's far too tempted by the vending machine in the foyer to follow her advice. Chanax believes Richard is their mysterious founder and follow his every whim, leading to their inevitable demise.

added.title: The Heart
added.description: When Mr. Robinson accidentally let slip how little he cares for Gumball and Darwin, they react by giving him the cold shoulder.  Surprisingly Mr. Robinson misses them and tries to win back their friendship. After a few failed attempts, Gumball and Darwin realize that Mr. Robinson's heart is protecting him, so they give it an intense affection overload.

added.title: The Return
added.description: Dad is in charge of getting the kids to their first day back at school on time, but he's overslept and now he can't find Gumball, Darwin or Anais anywhere. He sets about retracing his steps from the day before to work out where they might be.

added.title: The Money
added.description: The Wattersons have run out of money and are torn between being broke and selling out. Richard has lost all of the family's money. Nicole is happy for the Wattersons to appear in a Joyful Burger commercial for some much needed cash. However Gumball protests as he is convinced it's selling out. He persuades the family to stick to their principles, but they find sticking to a tiny budget even harder.

added.title: Council of the Creek
added.description: The circle game wreaks havoc on the Creek, so Craig forms a council to restore order.

added.title: Sparkle Cadet
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP team up with an intergalactic hero named Sparkle Cadet, hoping to save the Creek from negativity.

added.title: Cousin of the Creek
added.description: Craig takes his cousin, Bryson, to the Creek, and accidentally starts a water balloon war.

added.title: Camper on the Run
added.description: A runaway from a summer camp ends up at the Stump, but Craig suspects her story may not be what it seems.

added.title: Stink Bomb
added.description: An accidental stink bomb explosion causes the kids to evacuate the Creek, but Craig takes it upon himself to rescue those left behind in the stench.

added.title: The Evolution of Craig
added.description: Craig rescues a tadpole and decides to raise him into a level 100 frog!

added.title: Mortimor to the Rescue
added.description: When Craig, Kelsey and JP get stranded in murky water, it's up to Mortimor to save the day!

added.title: Secret in a Bottle
added.description: Craig needs to get a secret off his chest, so he pays a visit to the Keeper of Secrets in the Creek.

added.title: Trading Day
added.description: After Craig accidentally destroys a shipment of rare Chocorolls at the Trading Tree, Kit makes him work off his debt by running her trades throughout the Creek!

added.title: Crisis at Elder Rock
added.description: Tragedy strikes the Creek when the Elders get trapped under Elder Rock, and it's up to Craig, Kelsey and JP to rescue them.

added.title: A New Life
added.description: Apple and Onion both leave their homes and follow their dreams to the big city but things don't go quite to plan.

added.title: The Perfect Team
added.description: Onion worries his relationship with Apple is in jeopardy when a stray cat enters the picture.

added.title: Tips
added.description: Apple and Onion have to find a way to ride the Hot Air Balloon which is in their town for one day only.

added.title: Falafel's Fun Day
added.description: When Falafel decides to pack up and leave the city, Apple and Onion have to convince him to stay or they'll have to leave too.

added.title: Apple's in Trouble
added.description: Apple is challenged to a fight by a grumpy Cheesesteak, so he and Onion go on a quest to find the source of Cheesesteak's grumpiness.

added.title: 4 on 1
added.description: Onion's fear of crowds threatens his basketball team's success.

added.title: Hotdog's Movie Premiere
added.description: Apple and Onion square off against a no-nonsense security guard after they're banned from the premiere of their friend Hot Dog's new movie.

added.title: Bottle Catch
added.description: Apple and Onion's favorite game attracts some unexpected attention.

added.title: Pancake's Bus Tour
added.description: Apple and Onion go on a guided bus tour as part of their plan to get Apple's shoe back.

added.title: Block Party
added.description: Apple and Onion have to outwit a mean duck who's taken over their building's roof.

added.title: Apple's Focus
added.description: Apple decides to help Onion achieve his dream of competing on a baking show.

added.title: Lil Noodle
added.description: Apple and Onion must remain legit enough to be in their favorite rapper's music video.

added.title: Gyranoid of the Future
added.description: Apple and Onion are dead set on riding Gyranoid of the Future, the craziest roller coaster at the carnival.

added.title: Fun Proof
added.description: Apple and Onion want to become this week's "Most Fun People".

added.title: Whale Spotting
added.description: In order to see a rare whale, Apple and Onion have to become members of an exclusive club, but one of them doesn't quite have the chops.

added.title: Your Mother and Mine
added.description: Steven takes Garnet to meet some of his new friends.

added.title: I Am My Mom
added.description: Steven struggles to fix his mistakes.

added.title: Say Uncle
added.description: A long lost relative of Steven's comes to town to aid him in unlocking the power of his mother's Gem!

added.title: Story for Steven
added.description: Greg tells Steven the full story of how he met Rose-Quartz.

added.title: Shirt Club
added.description: Steven and Buck Dewey make t-shirts together.

added.title: Love Letters
added.description: Steven and Connie help Jamie the mailman with love.

added.title: Reformed
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Garnet chase after a monster that's been loose in the Temple.

added.title: Sworn to the Sword
added.description: Connie trains with Pearl to be a swordfighter.

added.title: Rising Tides, Crashing Skies
added.description: Ronaldo does some investigative reporting on whether Steven and the Crystal Gems are safe for Beach City.

added.title: Keeping It Together
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems revisit the Kindergarten and find a dark secret.

added.title: We Need to Talk
added.description: Greg tells Steven and Connie the story of how he learned about Gem fusion.

added.title: Chille Tid
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems try to relax with a slumber party.

added.title: Cry for Help
added.description: Steven's favorite TV show gets interrupted by a magical disturbance.

added.title: Lion 3: Straight to Video
added.description: Lion won't stop laying on Steven's face while he sleeps.

added.title: Rose's Scabbard
added.description: Steven joins Pearl on a special mission to a place that belonged to Rose-Quartz.

added.title: A Very Special Episode
added.description: Rainbow Quartz 2.0 promised to hang out with Onion the same day Sunstone scheduled a home safety Geminar! How can Steven be in two places, and two fusions, at once?

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: Finn the Human
added.description: After chasing the Lich through the portal, Finn and Jake meet a wishmaster named Prismo.

added.title: Jake the Dog
added.description: Jake and Prismo watch from the portal as the Ice King's crown makes Finn more and more powerful.

added.title: The Great Bird Man
added.description: Finn and Jake get lost in the badlands and are saved by Xergiok, ex-Goblin King who now lives in cave.

added.title: Simon & Marcy
added.description: A look at what Ice King and Marceline were like 996 years ago.

added.title: A Glitch Is a Glitch
added.description: Ice King creates a computer virus to delete everybody except him and Princess Bubblegum.

added.title: Puhoy
added.description: Stuck inside the treehouse during a sword storm, Jake builds a pillow fort while Finn goes to a different world.

added.title: BMO Lost
added.description: BMO gets snatched away by a giant eagle and must find his way home.

added.title: Princess Potluck
added.description: Ice King gets super jealous when he finds out that he wasn't invited to the Princess Potluck.

added.title: James Baxter the Horse
added.description: Finn and Jake meet a horse with the power to make sad people happy.

added.title: Shh!
added.description: Finn and Jake hold a contest to see who can last longer without talking.

added.title: The Suitor
added.description: Peppermint Butler thinks Princess Bubblegum is spending too much time in her lab and decides she needs a suitor.

added.title: One Last Job
added.description: Jake Jr. gets mixed up with some bad eggs and Jake has to reunite with his old gang for one last job to save him.

added.title: Conquest of Cuteness
added.description: King Snuggadoodle and the Huggaboopies invade Finn and Jake's tree house.

added.title: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
added.description: Finn gets caught up in trying to make everyone happy.

added.title: Rainy Day Daydream
added.description: Jake's imagination runs wild and Finn has to stop it before it kills them.

added.title: Maxin' and Relaxin'
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a mix tape from his parents' house.

added.title: Park Managers' Lunch
added.description: The park guys want to make sure Benson gets back safe from his lunch with Gene.

added.title: Mordecai and Rigby Down Under
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to catch a flight to the USA.

added.title: Married and Broke
added.description: Muscle Man and Starla want to win a game show to pay for their wedding.

added.title: I See Turtles
added.description: Eileen and the gang want to see baby sea turtles hatch and go into the ocean.

added.title: Format Wars II
added.description: The Discmasters have to end the Format Wars once and for all.

added.title: Happy Birthday Song Contest
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to win a happy birthday song contest.

added.title: Benson's Suit
added.description: Benson wants to feel better about himself.

added.title: Gamers Never Say Die
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to find a rare, golden video game patch.

added.title: 1000th Chopper Flight Party
added.description: Mordecai wants to share a piece of cake with C.J.

added.title: Party Horse
added.description: The guys want to help Party Horse pass his U.S. history test.

added.title: Brilliant Century Duck Crisis Special
added.description: The park guys want to get rid of a very large bird in the park.

added.title: A Bunch of Full Grown Geese
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get rid of some geese that are causing problems at the park.

added.title: My Mom
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are forced to work under Muscle Man and endure his repetitive jokes.

added.title: A Bunch of Baby Ducks
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby come across a family of ducks living in a fountain at the park and take quite a shine to them.

added.title: Spoooooky Game
added.description: The gang's weekly board game night has been getting a little too competitive lately, so when Unikitty finds a spooky old board game that's clearly haunted, their desire to win gets turned upside down, but cursed or not, they'll be the first to the finish line!

added.title: Sparkle Matter Matters
added.description: Unikitty learns that boring, old Richard has never produced any happy Sparkle Matter ever, she cooks up a formula with Dr. Fox that will overload him with emotions! Now, he's making so much Sparkle Matter it's threatening to destroy the kingdom! Can Unikitty help Richard find emotional balance before all is lost?

added.title: No Day Like Snow Day
added.description: When a blizzard hits the town, Master Frown tries to ruin everyone's fun by pretending to be a magical snowman! But when he gets frozen inside, Master Frown must worry less about ruining everyone's good time and instead not turning into a Frown-sicle, while he's forced to experience the joys of the holiday season!

added.title: Action Forest
added.description: Hawkodile is the toughest action hero in the land, until his old rival shows up to take vengeance on him. Defeated and in need of help, Hawkodile must train Unikitty and the others into super muscle­y tough bros. And there's only one place unstoppable warriors are made, the Action Forest.

added.title: Kaiju Kitty
added.description: When a giant monster attacks the Unikingdom, the gang fights back with Dr. Fox's awesome new secret weapon: a massive mega robot! But after the threat is contained, Unikitty doesn't want to stop using the  awesome robot, so she finds excuses for them to use it for everything, no matter how pointless. But what if the greatest threat to the kingdom turns out to be them?

added.title: Fire & Nice
added.description: When Master Frown causes Unikitty to have an angry outburst that gets a little too destructive, she wishes her Rage Kitty side wasn't part of her anymore. Thanks to a new Dr. Fox invention, she gets her wish: Rage Kitty and Nice Unikitty split apart into two! But with Unikitty now unable to get angry, she learns bottling up your anger is never a good thing.

added.title: Rock Friend
added.description: Unikitty discovers Puppycorn's only other friend is a boring old rock. Encouraged to "make more friends," Puppycorn just can't find someone he clicks with, until he takes her advice and decides to literally make a new friend out of the best parts of his friends. This won't go well.

added.title: Kitchen Chaos
added.description: After a workplace injury, Richard is unable to do his servant work. Unikitty and the others take on the task of one simple chore, clean the kitchen. This incredibly boring task taxes our heroes as they find every way possible to not do it. Will they be able to accomplish this goal and bring Richard back?

added.title: Crushing Defeat
added.description: When Hawkodile develops a secret crush on Dr. Fox, he finds himself actually crushing down in size! With Hawkodile too embarrassed to tell her (or anyone) about it, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings before he shrinks away into nothing!

added.title: Wishing Well
added.description: When Puppycorn uses a wishing well and it doesn't come true, Unikitty is shocked to discover the reason: all the wishes made over the years can't be granted because they're trapped at the bottom of the well (it's a dumb system.) She frees them to bring joy to the town… only to discover that they've gone a little bad after years trapped in a dark hole. Soon, they wish it would end!

added.title: Hide N' Seek
added.description: Unikitty is proud to be the reigning champ of Hide N' Seek Day. But when Unikitty finds everyone in the kingdom except for Richard, she hunts him down at all costs. Will Richard continue to elude the Princess at her favorite game, and if so, how?!

added.title: Stuck Together
added.description: When Master Frown's head is stuck on Unikitty's butt, she vows to help him get his own body back, but first, she has to attend to her nice princess duties! But sharing a body with Master Frown can get pretty complicated, especially when Master Frown has his own agenda.

added.title: Little Prince Puppycorn
added.description: Puppycorn finally realizes he's a prince, so he wants to be in charge of the kingdom for once! Despite their friends' concerns, Unikitty makes Puppycorn ruler but realizes absolute power in the hands of the pup is too much for him to handle and his ideas aren't exactly great. Can they remove him from power while keeping the kingdom from revolting?

added.title: Pet Pet
added.description: Unikitty and the gang bring home a tiny creature they name Pet Pet, but Richard won't let them keep it if they can't prove they are responsible owners. But when Pet Pet runs away, Unikitty must pretend to be Pet Pet until they can find him, or Richard will never let them have Pet Pet (or any pet) ever again! Will Unikitty survive pet training, or finally admit responsibility is a lot harder than she thought?

added.title: Kitty Court
added.description: When Unikitty has a little auto incident with Master Frown, he insists on taking it to court! Frown's thrilled. There's nothing worse than boring old court and he can't wait to subject Unikitty to it! Unikitty is happy to make things right but the trial will be in Unikitty Court, which is so nonsensical and fun. It's Frown's worst nightmare! Will Master Frown succeed in bumming Unikitty out? Or will he be the one punished by their legal antics?

added.title: Members Only
added.description: When the girls try to join an all-male superhero organization, they learn that sometimes supermen aren't so super.

added.title: Nano of the North
added.description: It's raining in Townville, but this is more than just rain. These drops are actually microscopic robots tearing apart the city, and the girls must find a way to fight them on their own level.

added.title: Film Flam
added.description: A sleazy director arrives in Townsville to make a film about the Powerpuff Girls. But this Hollywood type wants more out of Townsville than an Oscar-winning film.

added.title: Get Back Jojo
added.description: Mojo goes back in time to try and stop the Professor from having the inspiration for the perfect little girls. Little does he know that in doing so he provides just the spark the young Professor needs.

added.title: Monstra-City/Shut the Pup Up
added.description: Monstra-city: When all the monsters move from Monster Isle to Townsville, it's up to the Girls to keep the peace./Shut the Pup Up: When the Talking Dog witnesses a crime, he moves in with the girls for protection. But the girls soon realize this chatterbox dog is less than the perfect pet.

added.title: Toast of the Town/Divide and Conquer
added.description: Toast of the Town: When the Mayor rubs Chemical X on his head for hair growth, all of him grows and stomps through Townsville./Divide and Conquer: When the Amoeba Boys learn how to divide, they multiply wreaking havoc as the many amoebas descend upon Townsville.

added.title: Stray Bullet
added.description: In order to save an innocent squirrel, Bubbles gives him a dash of Chemical X, giving him some super squirrel powers.

added.title: Knock It Off
added.description: When the Professor's college roommate sees his old pal's brilliant creations, he decides to cash in on the popularity of the Powerpuffs.

added.title: Power-Noia
added.description: The girls have become paralyzed by their greatest fears. Who could be behind such an evil trick?

added.title: Forced Kin
added.description: A terrible, evil menace from outer space descends upon Townville. The girls must fight evil with evil so they seek the advice of Mojo Jojo.

added.title: Superfriends
added.description: The new girl next door learns it's hard to be best friends with superheroes and soon starts hanging out with the wrong kind of kid, Princess.

added.title: All Chalked Up
added.description: Him tricks Bubbles into bringing her chalk drawings to life, who then proceed to wreak havoc in Townsville.

added.title: Helter Shelter/Power Lunch
added.description: Helter Shelter: Bubbles has a habit of saving helpless animals and the Professor is sick of it. When Bubbles brings a baby whale home, she and her sisters have a whale of a time hiding this new addition./Power Lunch: The Gangreen Gang shoplifts from a mini-mart, shoveling loads of food down their throats as fast as possible. When the girls fire at them with their laser vision, a strange reaction occurs.

added.title: Keen on Keane/Not So Awesome Blossom
added.description: Keen on Keane: It's Valentine's Day and the girls notice that Ms. Keane is all alone. Time for a little matchmaking, but who will be the lucky fella?/Not So Awesome Blossom: When Blossom's attack plans fail one after the other, she loses confidence in herself as the group's leader.

added.title: Him Diddle Riddle
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls must solve a series of Him's riddles to keep the Professor from having to pay.

added.title: The Last Donnycorn
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn is hunted by a seemingly unstoppable foe, the Powerpuff Girls have to find a way to save him before it's too late!

added.title: Green Wing
added.description: When volunteering at a retirement home, Buttercup meets an old woman who claims she used to be a superhero.

added.title: 15 Minutes of Fame
added.description: When Bubbles' video goes viral, she goes to great lengths to maintain her status as a big-time director.

added.title: Splitsville
added.description: The girls learn to appreciate each others's style after having to each fight solo.

added.title: Clawdad
added.description: While visiting the lake, Buttercup vows to capture a legendary uncatchable crawdad.

added.title: A Star is Blossom
added.description: When Bubbles gets the lead in the school play, Blossom's jealousy consumes her.

added.title: Mini Golf Madness
added.description: Buttercup takes her game winning mini golf ball, in spite of ominous warnings of dire consequences.

added.title: The Tell Tale Schedulebot
added.description: After Blossom and Buttercup break Schedulebot, they'll do anything to keep the truth from coming out.

added.title: Buttercup vs. Math
added.description: When Buttercup tests into Honors Math, she tries to avoid being labeled a nerd.

added.title: Monkey Love
added.description: When Blossom makes a bad call, she becomes afraid to try again.

added.title: Bridezilla
added.description: When Mojo and Barbarus announce their wedding, the girls are convinced that they're up to no good.

added.title: Find Your Bliss
added.description: When Bubbles blames a string of accidents on her imaginary friend Bliss, her sisters begin to think she's lost her mind.

added.title: Bliss Reminisce
added.description: The Girls learn Bliss' backstory from the Professor, Mojo Jojo, and Bliss herself.

added.title: Blisster Sister
added.description: The Girls hang out with their new big sister Bliss, who gets a taste of fighting bad guys as part of the Powerpuff Girls.

added.title: Breaking Bliss
added.description: When Bliss struggles to control her powers an evil force arises to take advantage.

added.title: Hot Sauce
added.description: A quest for their favorite hot sauce causes the Bears to get involved with a sting operation.

added.title: Mom App
added.description: Hoping to finally get the mom-experience, the Bears use an app that'll bring a mom right to their door.

added.title: The Limo
added.description: To help distract Panda from his girl problems, Grizz and Ice Bear treat him to a ride in a limo.

added.title: More Everyone's Tube
added.description: Through another video browsing session online, we get more videos uploaded by the Bears and their friends.

added.title: Money Man
added.description: The Bears help Chloe present her project for a college science contest. But Chloe's rival makes things difficult.

added.title: Rescue Ranger
added.description: Tabes helps the Bears rescue Charlie after he gets captured by a villainous game hunter.

added.title: El Oso
added.description: In a flashback to long ago, Charlie has an adventure in the Mexican desert.

added.title: Escandalosos
added.description: The Baby Bears enter a Mexican wrestling tournament.

added.title: Pizza Band
added.description: The Bears get pizza at Papa Bear's Pizza Cave and wind up replacing the place's animatronic band. They're such a hit that they go on tour!

added.title: Adopted
added.description: The Baby Bears get adopted by an eccentric millionaire and get to live in his mansion.

added.title: Wingmen
added.description: In order to get some sleep, the Bears help an annoying bird find a new mate.

added.title: Braces
added.description: When the Bears go to the dentist, Panda gets braces. But, Panda finds out his braces grant him super abilities and the power goes to his head.

added.title: Christmas Movies
added.description: On Christmas Eve, the Baby Bears defend a video store from getting robbed.

added.title: Imaginary Friend
added.description: The Baby Bears invent an imaginary friend, but the trouble he causes is all too real.

added.title: Panda's Birthday
added.description: For Panda's Birthday, the Bears try to help Panda meet his favorite K-Pop band, Monsta X.

added.title: Motel
added.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

added.title: Rock Show
added.description: Chad's band Dogmon, plays a show for the first time in years, giving Clarence and Mary a chance to really rock out.

added.title: Karate Mom
added.description: After surprising Clarence with Martial Arts classes at the "Aberdojo," Mary gets talked into joining the class herself. She loves the slow-paced lessons in discipline and control, but Clarence just wants to have fun and kick butt! Can Mary convince Clarence to stick with the class, earn his belt and have some fun with her?

added.title: The Interrogation
added.description: After Mr. Reese discovers his precious car smeared with meatball sauce, he pulls out his officer's cap and enlists Clarence to help his investigation to nab the culprit.

added.title: Lost Playground
added.description: When Aberdale Elementary's beloved playground equipment is replaced with safe, boring alternatives, Clarence and the gang seek out their old playground equipment in the legendary lost playground yard.

added.title: Bird Boy Man
added.description: Sumo discovers an injured roadrunner, names him Hot Sauce, and nurses him back to health. The two become inseparable pals, but Sumo learns that a wild animal can't be contained.

added.title: Freedom Cactus
added.description: Clarence draws a comic for the school paper and it becomes a huge hit with the kids. When angry parents step in and censor the comic's crass humor, Clarence must stand up for his artistic vision.

added.title: Plane Excited
added.description: Clarence is all excited visit his grandma when he learns that Chad has never been on a plane. Clarence makes it his mission to help Chad get through a hectic flight.

added.title: Escape from Beyond the Cosmic
added.description: When Clarence accidentally breaks a local arcade game Jeff has become obsessed with, Clarence puts together his own real-life version of the game at home, encouraging Jeff to act out his fantasy in levels created exclusively by Clarence.

added.title: Ren Faire
added.description: Clarence and his pals venture to the Aberdale Renaissance Faire. Clarence confuses a medieval play for reality, and vows to stop the evil black knight from getting the princess.

added.title: Time Crimes
added.description: When Clarence is convinced he has the power to manipulate time he vows to only use his abilities for good. However, a day at school puts his morals to the test when he's given the ultimate choice to help his friends or pause time in the name of fun.

added.title: Saturday School
added.description: After creating an unapproved mural on a wall at Aberdale Elementary, Clarence, Jeff and Sumo are forced to come to school on a Saturday to clean up as punishment.

added.title: Attack the Block Party
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo investigate a high school party down the street, which they mistake for an alien invasion.

added.title: Hurricane Dilliss
added.description: Things in the Wendle household are turned upside down when Mary's mom Dyllis comes to visit, butting her way into every corner of Clarence, Mary and Chad's life.

added.title: Belly Bros
added.description: When a kid is bummed that his favorite shirt won't fit over his big belly, it's up to Uncle Grandpa to show him that t-shirts come and go, but having a big belly is always cool.

added.title: Tiger Trails
added.description: In the final moments of helping a kid, Uncle Grandpa just needs his trusty Giant Realistic Flying Tiger, but when he finds out she's gone, it sends UG on a journey to find the tiger and figure out why she left.

added.title: Space Emperor
added.description: When UG mistakes a kid in a costume for an evil space emperor, he sends him to another dimension where he becomes an actual evil space emperor and UG must figure out some way to bring him home.

added.title: Funny Face
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa accidentally unleashes a floating Funny Face that's so funny you laugh yourself to insanity, the guys realize that only Gus' seriousness can save them, but will he help them after they've hurt his feelings?

added.title: Moustache Cream
added.description: When UG and the gang are in a rush to purchase some emergency moustache cream, they face a formidable foe: Mart Mart.

added.title: Nickname
added.description: When a kid wants a cool nickname, UG tells him he has to earn it in the most legendary way ever: yard work!

added.title: Driver's Test
added.description: When a girl has trouble passing her driving test, Uncle Grandpa shows up to help her.  But when they accidentally set a Crazy Baby loose in the city, it's up to Uncle Grandpa to stop it... by teaching the girl how to drive!

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Sitter
added.description: Gus and Pizza Steve have plans to go out for the night, but UG can't be left alone in the RV, so they need a babysitter.  But when none are available, they turn to UG to babysit himself.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Ate My Homework
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa shows up and mistakenly eats a kid's Egyptian diorama for school, he helps the kid bring an actual pyramid to class, but accidentally unleashes an evil mummy on the world.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa for a Day
added.description: When UG gets his head stuck in a peanut butter jar, Mr. Gus and Pizza Steve have to pretend to be UG and help a kid.

added.title: Afraid of the Dark
added.description: When UG helps a little girl who is afraid of the dark, he convinces her there's nothing to be afraid of but their imaginations.  But when their imaginations prove to be pretty terrifying, they go on a quest to turn on the lights.

added.title: Treasure Map
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang don't have money to pay for their meal at a restaurant.  But when they discover a treasure map, it could be the answer to all their problems.  Too bad the treasure map is actually a restaurant activity placemat.

added.title: Locked Out
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets locked out of his RV and accidentally sets off the security system, it's up to him and his friends to disarm it before it destroys them.

added.title: Jorts
added.description: When Mr. Gus gets stuck in an embarrassingly super tight pair of jorts, he has to somehow get out of them in order to save his friends.

added.title: Brain Game
added.description: Uncle Grandpa calls on Pizza Steve, the self-proclaimed master of video games, to help a kid beat a game.  Only problem: Pizza Steve is terrible at video games.

added.title: El Rival
added.description: Volvemos a la época en la que Anaís era una bebé recién nacida, y los celos de Gumball y Darwin desatan una guerra de bebés.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Dama
added.description: Los niños descubren que Papá se ha vestido como una mujer para conocer amigos.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Tonto
added.description: Darwin termina en la sala de detención con el Chico Bomba, que decide convertir a Darwin en su nuevo blanco. Sin embargo, el ataque se vuelve en su contra cuando Darwin le arruina la vida.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Los Vegetales
added.description: Gumball y Darwin solo quieren holgazanear todo el día, pero terminan teniendo que salvar al resto de la familia.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Elegido
added.description: Tobías intenta ser el mejor amigo de Gumball.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Padre
added.description: Los niños intentan ayudar a Papá a hacerse amigo de Frankie.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Incomodidad
added.description: Gumball y Chico Salchicha descubren por qué se sienten tan incómodos el uno con el otro.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Jaula
added.description: Los niños convencen al Sr. Corneille de que se suba a un cuadrilátero y le organizan una pelea contra un temible luchador ruso.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Fe
added.description: Alan perdió su fe en la humanidad y puso el mundo blanco y negro. Gumball tiene que superar el odio que siente hacia Alan para recuperar el color a través del canto.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Candidato
added.description: Un grupo de niños quedan encerrados en la escuela luego de la gala de caridad de sus padres. Designan a Gumball como líder encargado de sacarlos de ahí, pero la situación se convierte en un caos.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Cerebro
added.description: La familia tiene que dejar de hacer cosas estúpidas para impedir que Anaís entre en coma por darse tantas palmadas faciales en señal de exasperación.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Fundador
added.description: Papá desata un caos en el edificio Chanax cuando lo confunden con el presidente de la empresa, desaparecido hace tiempo. Mamá y un empleado insatisfecho deben salvar a todos de las ideas peligrosas de Richard.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Corazon
added.description: El señor Robinson intenta recuperar la amistad de Gumball y Darwin y falla una y otra vez.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Regreso
added.description: Es el primer día de clases, pero Gumball y Darwin no aparecen por ningún lado.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Salsa Picante
added.description: La búsqueda de su salsa picante favorita hace que los Osos se involucren en una operación de picadura.

added.title: Mama a la Orden
added.description: Con el deseo de tener la experiencia de una madre, los osos usan una aplicación que les traerá una madre a la puerta de sus casas.

added.title: La Limosna
added.description: Para ayudar a Panda a distraerse de sus problemas románticos, Pardo y Polar le regalan un paseo en limosina.

added.title: Mas del canal de todos
added.description: A través de otra sesión de navegación por Internet, vemos más videos subidos por los Osos y sus amigos.

added.title: El Benefactor
added.description: Los Osos ayudan a Chloe a presentar su proyecto de ciencias para un concurso escolar. Pero el rival de Chloe complica las cosas.

added.title: Los Rescatadores
added.description: Cuando un cazador malvado captura a Charlie, Tabes ayuda a los Osos a rescatarlo.

added.title: El Oso
added.description: En flashes retrospectivos al pasado lejano, vemos una aventura de Charlie en el desierto mexicano.

added.title: Escandalosos
added.description: Los Osos bebé se inscriben en un torneo de lucha libre mexicana.

added.title: La Banda Pizzera
added.description: Los Osos van a comer a la Cabaña de la Pizza de Papá Oso y terminan reemplazando la banda animatrónica del local. iSon tan exitosos que terminan saliendo de gira!

added.title: Adoptados
added.description: Un millonario excéntrico adopta a los Osos bebé y los lleva a vivir a su mansión.

added.title: Acompanantes
added.description: Para poder dormir un poco, los Osos ayudan a un ave molesta a encontrar una nueva pareja.

added.title: Frenos
added.description: Cuando los Osos van al dentista, Panda se coloca frenos. Pronto, descubre que los frenos le confieren habilidades superiores y ese poder se le sube a la cabeza.

added.title: Peliculas Navidenas
added.description: En Nochebuena, los Osos bebé impiden un robo en una tienda de videos.

added.title: Amigo Imaginario
added.description: Los Osos bebé inventan un nuevo amigo imaginario, pero los problemas que genera son demasiado reales.

added.title: El Cumpleanos de Panda
added.description: Para el cumpleaños de Panda, los Osos intentan ayudarlo a conocer a su banda favorita de K-pop, Monsta X.

added.title: El consejo del Arroyo
added.description: El juego del circulo siembra el caos en el Arroyo, así que Craig forma un consejo para restaurar el orden.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Cadete Destello
added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP forman equipo con una heroína intergaláctica llamada Cadete Destello, con la esperanza de salvar al Arroyo de la negatividad.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Primo del Arroyo
added.description: Craig lleva a su primo Bryson al Arroyo, donde accidentalmente inicia una guerra de globos de agua.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Campista Profuga
added.description: Una fugitiva de un campamento de verano termina en el Tronco, pero Craig sospecha que su historia puede no ser lo que parece.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Bomba apestosa
added.description: La explosión accidental de una bomba de olor causa que todos los niños evacúen el Arroyo, pero Craig toma la responsabilidad de rescatar a aquellos dejados atrás en el hedor.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Evolucion de Craig
added.description: iCraig rescata a un renacuajo y decide criarlo hasta que sea una rana nivel 100!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Crisis en la roca de Ancianos
added.description: Una tragedia azota al Arroyo cuando los Ancianos quedan atrapados bajo la Roca Anciana. Ahora Craig, Kelsey y JP deben rescatarlos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El secreto en la botella
added.description: Craig necesita compartir un secreto con alguien, por lo que visita al Guardián de los Secretos en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Dia de trueque
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Craig destruye un cargamento de chocolates poco comunes en el árbol del trueque, Kit lo hace trabajar para pagar su deuda: idebe ocuparse de los intercambios de Kit por todo el bosque!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Mortimer al rescate
added.description: Cuando Craig, Kelsey y JP quedan varados en agua turbia, iMortimer debe salir al rescate!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Juego tenebroso
added.description: Últimamente, la noche semanal de juegos de mesa de la banda se volvió demasiado competitiva, así que cuando Unikitty encuentra un viejo y espeluznante juego de mesa que claramente está embrujado, los deseos de ganar del grupo quedan dados vuelta, pero con o sin embrujo, iquieren ser los primeros en cruzar la línea de llegada!

added.title: Una Nueva Vida
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín abandonan sus hogares y se mudan a la ciudad, donde se conocen por primera vez.

added.title: El Equipo Perfecto
added.description: A Cebollín le preocupa que su relación con Manzana corra peligro cuando un gato callejero entra en su vida.

added.title: La material de brillo importa
added.description: Cuando Unikitty se entera de que el viejo y aburrido Richard nunca produjo materia de brillo feliz, iprepara una fórmula con la Dra. Fox que lo sobrecargará de emociones! iAhora, Richard produce tanta materia de brillo que amenaza con destruir el reino! ¿Podrá Unikitty ayudar a Richard a encontrar el equilibrio emocional antes de que todo desaparezca?

added.title: Propinas
added.description: Luego de destruir por accidente el boleto de Falafel para un concierto, Manzana y Cebollín deben descubrir un modo de evitar la furia de Falafel.

added.title: Un dia nevado
added.description: Cuando una tormenta de nieve llega a la ciudad, Master Frown trata de arruinar la diversión de todos fingiendo ser un muñeco de nieve mágico. Pero cuando se congela por dentro, Master Frown debe preocuparse menos por arruinar la diversión de todos y más por no convertirse en un témpano malhumorado, imientras se ve obligado a experimentar la alegría de la temporada navideña!

added.title: El Dia Divertido de Falafel
added.description: Cuando Falafel decide empacar sus cosas e ir a la ciudad, Manzana y Cebollín deben convencerlo de quedarse.

added.title: Bosque de accion
added.description: Hawkodile es el héroe de acción más rudo de la zona, hasta que su viejo rival llega para vengarse de él. Derrotado y necesitado de ayuda, Hawkodile debe entrenar a Unikitty y a los otros para que se conviertan en compañeros superfuertes y musculosos. Y solo hay un lugar donde surgen guerreros imparables, el Bosque de Acción.

added.title: Gatita kaiju
added.description: Cuando un monstruo gigante ataca el Unireino, la banda se defiende con la impresionante nueva arma secreta de la Dra. Fox: iun mega robot gigantesco! Pero después de contener la amenaza, Unikitty no quiere dejar de usar el increíble robot, así que encuentra excusas para usarlo para todo, sin importar qué tan inútil sea. Pero, ¿y si ellos resultan ser la mayor amenaza para el reino?

added.title: Manzana esta en Problemas
added.description: Bistec con Queso, malhumorado, desafía a Manzana a una pelea. De ese modo, Manzana puede embarcarse con Cebollín en una misión para encontrar el origen del malhumor de Bistec con Queso.

added.title: Fuego y Hielo
added.description: Cuando Master Frown le provoca a Unikitty un ataque de ira que se vuelve demasiado destructivo, ella desea que su faceta de Rage Kitty ya no sea parte de ella. Gracias a un nuevo invento de la Dra. Fox, el E-MoteTV, la princesa consigue su deseo: iRage Kitty y Nice Unikitty se dividen en dos! Pero ahora que Unikitty es incapaz de enfadarse, aprende que reprimir la ira nunca es algo bueno.

added.title: Un Episodio Muy Especial
added.description: Cuarzo Arcoíris 2.0 prometió cuidar de Cebolla el mismo día que Heliolita programó una charla sobre la seguridad del hogar. ¿Es posible para Steven estar en dos lugares a la vez y ser dos fusiones al mismo tiempo?

added.title: 4 a 1
added.description: El temor de Cebollín a las multitudes amenaza el éxito de su equipo de baloncesto.

added.title: Amigo roca
added.description: Unikitty descubre que el único otro amigo de Puppycorn es una roca vieja y aburrida. Incentivado a ""hacer más amigos"", Puppycorn no puede encontrar a alguien con quien sienta afinidad, hasta que sigue el consejo de Unikitty y decide literalmente hacer un nuevo amigo con las mejores partes de sus amigos. Esto no irá bien.

added.title: Hot Dog Estrena su Pelicula
added.description: Cuando unos guardias de seguridad muy serios los echan del estreno de la nueva película de su amigo Hot Dog, Manzana y Cebollín se preparan para pelear.

added.title: Dia de Nevada
added.description: Steven y las Gemas de Cristal tienen la oportunidad de ponerse al día en un día nevado.

added.title: Caos en la cocina
added.description: Después de lesionarse en su lugar de trabajo, Richard no puede hacer sus tareas de criado. Unikitty y los demás se encargan de una simple tarea: limpiar la cocina. Esta actividad increíblemente aburrida es un desafío para nuestros héroes, que buscan todas las formas posibles de no hacerla. ¿Serán capaces de alcanzar esta meta y traer de regreso a Richard?

added.title: Porque tan triste?
added.description: Steven ha escuchado rumores de un par de Gemas que todavía están destruyendo mundos. Si él no puede detenerlas, tal vez Lapis sí.

added.title: Atrapa la Botella
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín inventan un nuevo juego que atrae una atención inesperada.

added.title: Derrota aplastante
added.description: Cuando Hawkodile se enamora en secreto de la Dra. Fox, idescubre que comienza a encogerse en tamaño! Como está demasiado avergonzado como para contárselo a ella (o a cualquiera), Unikitty y la pandilla se convierten en sus gurús del amor para ayudarlo a confesar sus sentimientos antes de encogerse hasta desaparecer.

added.title: El Paseo en Autobus de Pancake
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín suben a un autobús que da un tour guiado como parte de su plan para recuperar el zapato de Manzana.

added.title: Pequena graduacion
added.description: Steven y las Gemas celebran la primera clase de graduados de la Escuela Madre.

added.title: Duo Espinoso
added.description: Después de dejar Pequeña Escuela Madre, Steven ha encontrado un nuevo pasatiempo: las plantas.

added.title: Fiesta en la Cuadra
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben ser más astutos que un pato malvado que se apoderó del techo de su edificio.

added.title: Pozo de los deseos
added.description: Cuando Puppycorn utiliza una fuente de los deseos y su deseo no se hace realidad, Unikitty se sorprende al descubrir la razón: todos los deseos realizados a lo largo de los años no se pueden cumplir porque están atrapados en el fondo de la fuente (es un sistema tonto). Unikitty los libera para que traigan alegría a la ciudad, y así descubre que se echaron a perder un poco después de años atrapados en un agujero oscuro. iPronto todos desearán que todo se termine!

added.title: Escondidas
added.description: Unikitty se enorgullece de ser la campeona del Día de la escondida. Pero cuando encuentra a todos en el reino excepto a Richard, lo busca a toda costa. ¿Seguirá Richard eludiendo a la princesa en su juego favorito y, si es así, cómo lo hará?

added.title: Manzana, Concentrate
added.description: Manzana ayuda a Cebollín a cumplir su sueño de competir en un programa de pastelería.

added.title: Fideito
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben seguir teniendo la onda suficiente para aparecer en el video musical de su rapero favorito.

added.title: Pegados
added.description: Cuando la cabeza de Master Frown se atasca en el cuerpo de Unikitty, ella promete ayudarlo a recuperar su antiguo cuerpo, ipero primero, tiene que ocuparse de sus deberes de princesa! Pero compartir un cuerpo con Master Frown puede ser bastante complicado, especialmente cuando él tiene sus propios planes en mente.

added.title: Principito perricornio
added.description: Puppycorn por fin se da cuenta de que es un príncipe, iy quiere estar a cargo del reino por una vez! A pesar de las preocupaciones de sus amigos, Unikitty permite que Puppycorn sea el rey, pero pronto, el poder absoluto en las manos del cachorro se le hace difícil de manejar, y sus ideas no son lo que se diría muy geniales. ¿Podrán removerlo del poder mientras evitan un levantamiento del pueblo?

added.title: Mascota
added.description: Unikitty y la pandilla traen a casa a una pequeña criatura a la que llaman Pet Pet, pero Richard no les permite quedársela si no pueden demostrar que son dueños responsables. Cuando Pet Pet se escapa, Unikitty debe fingir ser la mascota hasta que puedan encontrarlo, io Richard nunca les dejará tener a Pet Pet (o a cualquier mascota) de nuevo! ¿Sobrevivirá Unikitty al entrenamiento de mascotas, o terminará admitiendo que la responsabilidad es mucho más difícil de lo que pensaba?

added.title: Juicio Gatuno
added.description: Cuando Unikitty tiene un pequeño incidente automovilístico con Master Frown, iél insiste en llevar el tema a juicio! Frown está encantado: no hay nada peor que un tribunal viejo y aburrido, y está ansioso por someter a Unikitty a esa experiencia. A Unikitty le gusta hacer las cosas bien, pero el juicio se realizará en la corte de Unikitty, ique es tan absurda y divertida que se convierte en la peor pesadilla de Frown! ¿Master Frown logrará contagiar a Unikitty con su negatividad? ¿O será él quien termine castigado por las payasadas legales?

added.title: Pruebas de Diversion
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín quieren convertirse en la "Gente más divertida" de esta semana.

added.title: Avistamiento de Ballenas
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín necesitan unirse a un club exclusivo para ver una ballena fuera de lo común.

added.title: Gyranoide del Futuro
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín se esfuerzan por subir a la montaña rusa más loca del parque de diversiones.

removed.title: The Nom Nom Show
removed.description: Things go awry while Nom Nom shoots his first television show. The Bears offer to help and appear on the show.

removed.title: Little Dude
removed.description: While Finn and Jake go swimming, Finn's hat magically comes to life!

removed.title: House Guest
removed.description: After injuring his leg, Greg comes to live with Steven and unintentionally interferes with Steven's powers.

removed.title: Jeff Wins

removed.description: Steven attempts to build a spaceship to let Pearl revisit the wonders of the cosmos.

removed.title: Capullos de Rosa
removed.description: Steven recibe una visita sorpresa de algunos viejos amigos y una introducción aún más sorprendente a algunos nuevos.

removed.title: Cool Uncles
removed.description: The Titans take a trip to Wackadoodles, but Trigon makes Raven babysit her little brothers.

removed.title: El gran viaje
removed.description: Es hora de las vacaciones anuales de la banda, pero Halcondrilo se niega a ir, alegando que las vacaciones de la banda nunca son divertidas para él porque los otros son pésimos compañeros de vacaciones. removed.title: Island Adventure
removed.description: Steven takes Lars and Sadie on a vacation to a magical beach to mend their friendship.

removed.title: Creek Cart Racers
removed.description: A high-speed race with a high-stakes prize may be too much for Craig and his friends.

removed.title: Secret Team
removed.description: Steven, Amethyst and Pearl accidentally pop a bubbled gem and form Secret Team to secretly retrieve the missing shards.

removed.title: Criss Cross Crisis
removed.description: Another one of the Professor's plans goes awry when he tries to switch apples for oranges causing the entire town to switch from one body to another. The girls must remedy the situation.

removed.title: Career Day
removed.description: After an excessive spending spree, the Golden Goose tells the gang it won't give them any more golden eggs until they learn the value of money. Following Rick's advice to save money, the gang open a cookie shop to make money on their own and save it in a huge vault.

removed.title: Bubblevision/Bought and Scold
removed.description: Bubblevision: Bubbles' fighting has been really terribly lately and the Professor discovers she needs glasses. removed.title: Road Trippin'
removed.description: Realizing her and the Professor don't have much in common, Bubbles schedules a road trip with just the two of them.

removed.title: Get Active Dance
removed.description: Mei, Ella, animals and vegetables have a farm active day exercising and organising the farm

removed.title: Tent Trouble
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby must replace CJ's expensive tent before she realizes they destroyed it.

removed.title: Rose Buds
removed.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

removed.title: Mystery Dungeon
removed.description: Ice King, NEPTR, Tree Trunks, Shelby and Lemongrab are trapped inside a mysterious dungeon and must work together to free themselves.
